v1.0.0 — Initial stable release (2026-05-08)
First stable release of the Virtual Port Manager
- Provides persistent runit services for:
- socat‑ttyV0 (virtual serial port)
- dbus‑serialbattery‑ttyV0 (DBus integration)
- virtual‑port‑watchdog (health monitoring)
- Includes installer and uninstaller
- Adds rc.local boot integration
- Provides status.sh for health checks
- Supports Waveshare TCP bridge for JK‑PB BMS
- Fully validated on Raspberry Pi 2 Venus OS build

----------

v1.0.1 — Lifecycle control update (2026-05-10)
- Added enable.sh and disable.sh for clean service lifecycle control
- enable.sh: recreates /service symlinks and starts runit services
- disable.sh: stops services via svc -d and removes /service symlinks
- Ensured predictable start/stop behaviour across all three services
- Updated README with enable/disable instructions and lifecycle notes
- Validated clean transitions between enabled/disabled states
- Confirmed status.sh correctly reflects service state after lifecycle operations

----------

v1.0.2 - Refined enable.sh and disable.sh (2026-05-21)
- Improved enable.sh and disable.sh to ensure clean, idempotent lifecycle control
- Removed unintended blank‑line accumulation in /data/rc.local
- Added consistent marker‑based patching for both JK‑PB and watchdog blocks
- Ensured enable.sh restores both rc.local blocks reliably after disable
- Minor cosmetic and structural cleanup for maintainability
- Fixed README paths referencing old /data/apps/virtual-port directory
